22/12/2005
WASHINGTON, United States -- The US State Department says it welcomes the recent EU decision granting official candidate status to Macedonia. In a statement issued Wednesday (21 December), officials called it a positive signal to the rest of the Balkans.
Separately Wednesday, French President Jacques Chirac sent a letter of congratulations to Macedonian counterpart President Branko Crvenkovski, echoing that sentiment and urging continued reforms.
In other news, Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva visited Moscow on Wednesday. His Russian counterpart, Sergey Lavrov, congratulated Macedonia on its EU milestone. (Macedonian Government Web site - 22/12/05; US State Department, Makfax, Telma TV, RIA Novosti - 21/12/05)
